Split a population of genotypes randomly into several locations.

split_families.Rd

Split a populationof genotypes randomly into several locations, with the aim of having approximatelly the same number of replicates of each genotype, line or treatment per location.

split_families(l = NULL, data = NULL)

Arguments

l

Number of locations.
data

Data frame with the entry (ENTRY) and the labels of each treatment (NAME) and number of individuals per family group (FAMILY).

Value

A table with summary of cases.

A list with the entries for each location.
